<Routines>
<Routine Name="Logic" Type="RLL">
<RLLContent>
<Rung Number="0" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Disclaimer - All information provided  -- No warranty or implied merchantability.
Refer to the RSLogix 5000 End User License Agreement (EULA) in the Release Notes.

State 0: If Enable Instruction and Trigger Update Now are set, move to state 1 to start an update.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(0,State)XIC(Enable_Instruction)XIC(Trigger_Update_Now)OTU(Trigger_Update_Now)MOVE(1,State);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="1" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[State 0: Wait interval between updates.

Convert poll rate to milliseconds and write to timer preset.
Execute timer and populate the seconds countdown display.
If not leaving this state (timer not done), TND returns out of the AOI. this saves on scan time.
Go to state 1 when timer goes done.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(0,State)XIC(Enable_Instruction)GT(Query_Interval_in_Min,0)[[XIC(DN) ,EQ(Query_Error_Retry_in_Min,0) ] MUL(60000,Query_Interval_in_Min,Interval_Timer.PRE) ,XIC(ER) NE(Query_Error_Retry_in_Min,0) MUL(60000,Query_Error_Retry_in_Min,Interval_Timer.PRE) ,TON(Interval_Timer,?,?) ,CPT(Next_Query_in_Min,(Interval_Timer.PRE-Interval_Timer.ACC)/60000) ,XIO(Interval_Timer.DN) TND() ,XIC(Interval_Timer.DN) MOVE(1,State) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="2" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[State 1: Initialization.

Populate the path data in the path string.
Initialize message paths.
Initialize the destination IP for the message write instruction.
Initialize the message read and write timeout parameters.
Clear all instruction status bits and go to state 2.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(1,State)[MOVE(2,Module_Path.LEN) MOVE(1,Module_Path.DATA[0]) MOVE(Enet_Slot_Number,Module_Path.DATA[1]) ,COP(Module_Path,SKT_Create.Path,1) COP(Module_Path,SKT_Open.Path,1) ,COP(Module_Path,SKT_Read.Path,1) COP(Module_Path,SKT_Write.Path,1) COP(Module_Path,SKT_Delete.Path,1) ,MOVE(1000,MSG_Data.Write_Source.Timeout) MOVE(5000,MSG_Data.Read_Source.Timeout) ,OTU(ER) OTU(DN) OTL(EN) MOVE(2,State) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="3" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[State 2:   Create socket.

Execute message to create socket object.
Socket is created when message goes done.
Move the instance number of the socket into the read, write, and delete messages so they know what to reference. Go to state 3.
If message errors, go to state 0 to wait one inteval before trying again..
]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(2,State)[XIO(SKT_Create.EN) MSG(SKT_Create) ,XIC(SKT_Create.ER) OTL(ER) MOVE(0,State) ,XIC(SKT_Create.DN) [MOVE(MSG_Data.Instance,SKT_Write.Instance) MOVE(MSG_Data.Instance,SKT_Read.Instance) MOVE(3,State) ,MOVE(MSG_Data.Instance,SKT_Open.Instance) MOVE(MSG_Data.Instance,SKT_Delete.Instance) ] ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="4" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[State 3:   Connect socket.

Execute message to associate IP address or hostname to the remote device.
]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(3,State)[XIO(SKT_Open.EN) [CONCAT(Server_Address,Port,MSG_Data.Open_Connection.Dest_Addr) ADD(MSG_Data.Open_Connection.Dest_Addr.LEN,8,SKT_Open.REQ_LEN) ,MSG(SKT_Open) ] ,XIC(SKT_Open.ER) OTL(ER) MOVE(8,State) ,XIC(SKT_Open.DN) MOVE(4,State) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="5" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[State 4.  Write data.
The write message length must be set to 16 larger then the string size.
Go to state 5 when done or state 8 on error.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(4,State)[XIO(SKT_Write.EN) ADD(MSG_Data.Write_Source.Buffer.LEN,16,SKT_Write.REQ_LEN) MSG(SKT_Write) ,XIC(SKT_Write.ER) OTL(ER) MOVE(8,State) ,XIC(SKT_Write.DN) MOVE(5,State) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="6" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[State 5: Read data.

Go to state 6 when done, or state 8 on error.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(5,State)[XIO(SKT_Read.EN) MSG(SKT_Read) ,XIC(SKT_Read.ER) OTL(ER) MOVE(8,State) ,XIC(SKT_Read.DN) MOVE(6,State) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="7" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[State 6: Check data.

If data is not 48 bytes in length, then there is a data error. Goto state 8.
Otherwise, data should be ok, and goto state 7 to process it.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(6,State)[NE(MSG_Data.Read_Response.Data_Length,48) OTL(ER) MOVE(8,State) ,EQ(MSG_Data.Read_Response.Data_Length,48) MOVE(7,State) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="8" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[State 7: Interpret Time.

Byte swap data to match controller format. Convert SNTP time to real date.
The Date is then written to the controllers clock if "Write_to_controller_clock" is set.
The time difference between the controller clock and the NTP time is also calculated for user reference.
Goto state 8]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(7,State)[SWPB(MSG_Data.Read_Response.SNTP_Data.Transmitted_Time_Whole_Seconds,REVERSE,SNTP_Seconds.Sec) ,AOI_TIME_ADD(AOI_SNTP_Time_To_Current_Date,SNTP_Rollover_Date,SNTP_Seconds,UTC_Time) ,SWPB(MSG_Data.Read_Response.SNTP_Data.Transmitted_Time_Fractional_Seconds,REVERSE,MSG_Data.Read_Response.SNTP_Data.Transmitted_Time_Fractional_Seconds) ,BTD(MSG_Data.Read_Response.SNTP_Data.Transmitted_Time_Fractional_Seconds,4,temp,0,28) MUL(temp,3.725290298E-3,UTC_Time.uSec) ,GSV(WallClockTime,,DateTime,Time_Logix.Yr) AOI_TIME_DIFFERENCE(AOI_Time_Difference,Time_Logix,UTC_Time,Time_Logix_Drift) ,XIC(Sync_Controller_Clock) SSV(WallClockTime,,DateTime,UTC_Time.Yr) ,OTL(DN) MOVE(8,State) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="9" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[State 8: Delete the socket.

Go to state 0 after completion.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQ(8,State)OTU(EN)[MSG(SKT_Delete) ,[XIC(SKT_Delete.ER) ,XIC(SKT_Delete.DN) ] MOVE(0,State) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
</RLLContent>
</Routine>
<Routine Name="Prescan" Type="RLL">
<Description>
<![CDATA[Prescan]]>
</Description>
<RLLContent>
<Rung Number="0" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Sets/hardcodes the NTP Rollover date.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[[MOVE(2036,SNTP_Rollover_Date.Yr) MOVE(2,SNTP_Rollover_Date.Mo) MOVE(7,SNTP_Rollover_Date.Da) ,MOVE(6,SNTP_Rollover_Date.Hr) MOVE(16,SNTP_Rollover_Date.Sec) MOVE(28,SNTP_Rollover_Date.Min) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="1" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Reset all output bits and state.]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[OTU(EN)OTU(DN)OTU(ER)MOVE(0,State);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="2" Type="N">
<Text>
<![CDATA[MUL(60000,Query_Interval_in_Min,Interval_Timer.PRE);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
</RLLContent>
</Routine>
</Routines>
</AddOnInstructionDefinition>
<AddOnInstructionDefinition Name="PI_Saadin_JaP" Revision="1.1" Vendor="jAp" ExecutePrescan="false" ExecutePostscan="false" ExecuteEnableInFalse="false" CreatedDate="2011-06-28T11:46:32.500Z" CreatedBy="FI\JPetters" EditedDate="2016-11-23T10:39:47.328Z" EditedBy="FI\jnappi" SoftwareRevision="v20.01"
>
<Description>
<![CDATA[PI-SAADIN]]>
</Description>
<RevisionNote>
<![CDATA[Päivitysajan hallinta lisätty. Säädin tutkii mikä on minimi ja korjaa tarvittaessa]]>
</RevisionNote>
<AdditionalHelpText>
<![CDATA[P=Vahvistus. Yksikötön positiivinen reaaliluku

I= Aika sekunneissa, jossa säädin pyrkii kuromaan Setpointin ja Prosessiarvon eron umpeen

D= Aika sekunneissa, jonka päähän säädin ennustaa muutosnopeuden kiuhtyvyyden mukaan. Tulevaisuuden muutosnopeus otetaan siten huomioon että laskennassa käytetään Hetkellisen ja Ennustetun muutosnopeuden keskiarvoa]]>
</AdditionalHelpText>
